Program: Omnibus
Title: Barry Manilow
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376jr9
Last Broadcast Date: 20 December 1989
'There is more to Barry Manilow than sugary sweet ballads and a nice line in cuddly jumpers'. Famous for songs such as 'Mandy', 'Stay' and 'I Write the Songs', the jazz roots and early musical influences of the singer songwriter are traced here.